cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV. 

The paper presents a new deep learning model for traffic signal control, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning model for traffic signal control. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses deep learning techniques to optimize traffic signal control. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is another possible category as the paper deals with controlling traffic signals, which can be seen as a form of robotic control. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a state space approach to capture the main attributes of the control environment and the underlying temporal traffic movement patterns. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with analyzing traffic movement patterns.
